This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category as it presents a method for reinforcement learning using imitation learning. It also involves the use of domain confusion, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) categories as it deals with training agents to achieve goals in complex environments. The use of demonstrations and viewpoint also suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may be a relevant category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the software engineering (cs.SD) category as it involves the development of a method for training agents.
